        <h1>System monitoring procedures</h1>
        <h3>Check site operations</h3>
        <ol style="list-style: decimal;list-style-type: decimal;">
            <li class="p-ActionDetail" value="1">
                <p class="ActionDetail"><a href="#ControllareAllarmiEventi"> Checking alarms and events</a>
                </p>
            </li>
            <li class="p-ActionDetail" value="2">
                <p class="ActionDetail"><a href="#MonitorareImpianto">Monitoring the site</a>
                </p>
            </li>
        </ol>
        <h3>Editing parameters and devices</h3>
        <ul style="list-style: disc;" type="disc">
            <li class="p-ActionDetail" value="1">
                <p class="ActionDetail"><a href="#ModificareParametriServizio">Editing service parameters and devices</a>
                </p>
            </li>
        </ul>
        <h3>Print HACCP or log reports.</h3>
        <ul>
            <li style="list-style: disc;" type="disc" class="p-ActionDetail" value="1">
                <p class="ActionDetail"><a href="#RichiedereStampaReport"> Printing a HACCP and log report</a>
                </p>
            </li>
        </ul>
        <hr style="color: #808080;height: 1px;float: alignleft;" color="#808080" size="0" align="center" width="100%" />
        <p class="TitoloInterno">
            <img src="../Resources/Images/AAaction.gif" style="border: none;float: none;width: 32px;height: 32px;border-style: none;border-style: none;" width="32" height="32" border="0" /><a name="ControllareAllarmiEventi"></a> Checking alarms and events</p>
        <ol style="list-style: decimal;list-style-type: decimal;">
            <li class="p-ActionDetail" value="1">
                <p class="ActionDetail">Check for alarms
                                                            </p>
                <div>
                    <ul style="list-style: disc;" type="disc">
                        <li class="p" value="1">
                            <p>The icon <img src="../Resources/Images/menusx/multi_icon_y_32x41.png" style="border: none;float: none;border-style: none;border-style: none;width: 32;height: 41;" border="0" /> on the logon page indicates that there are current alarms.</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                    <p class="Image">
                        <img src="../Resources/Images/pvpro_logon_BELL.png" style="border: none;width: 350px;height: 234px;float: none;border-style: none;border-style: none;" width="350" height="234" border="0" />
                    </p>
                    <ul style="list-style: disc;" type="disc">
                        <li class="p" value="1">
                            <p>Enter the program, click on the icon <img src="../Resources/Images/menusx/multi_icon_y_32x41.png" style="border: none;float: none;border-style: none;border-style: none;width: 32;height: 41;" border="0" /> at the lower left: the current alarm page opens:</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>
                        <img src="../Resources/Images/AlarmBellGlobal_350x235.png" style="border: none;float: none;border-style: none;border-style: none;width: 350;height: 235;" border="0" />
                    </p>
                </div>
            </li>
            <li class="p-ActionDetail" value="2">
                <p class="ActionDetail">Check and print global alarms
                                                            </p>
                <div>
                    <ul style="list-style: disc;" type="disc">
                        <li class="p" value="1">
                            <p>In <span style="font-weight: bold;">ALARMS/EVENTS, <span style="font-weight: bold;">Alarm </span> list </span> check and print triggered alarms (see chapter<a href="Allarmi__allarmi_attivi.htm"> Active alarms</a>).</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="p" value="2">
                            <p>Double-click an alarm to open details and acknowledge the alarm or stop actions or force clear if the alarm is insignificant (see chapter <a href="Allarmi__dettaglio_allarme.htm">Alarm details</a>)</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="p" value="3">
                            <p>In <span style="font-weight: bold;">ALARMS/EVENTS</span>, <span style="font-weight: bold;">Cleared alarms</span> page, check and print cleared alarms and double-click to open alarm details (see chapter <a href="Allarmi__allarmi_rientrati.htm">Cleared alarms</a>).</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </li>
            <li class="p-ActionDetail" value="3">
                <p class="ActionDetail">Check and print global events
                                                            </p>
                <div>
                    <ul style="list-style: disc;" type="disc">
                        <li class="p" value="1">
                            <p>In <span style="font-weight: bold;">ALARMS/EVENTS, Event list</span> check and print the event sequence, starting from the most recent event (probably near the date-time of the first alarm) to the event that caused the alarm (see chapter <a href="Eventi__introduzione.htm">Events</a>).</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </li>
            <li class="p-ActionDetail" value="4">
                <p class="ActionDetail">If necessary, run a targeted search
                                                            </p>
                <div>
                    <ul style="list-style: disc;" type="disc">
                        <li class="p" value="1">
                            <p>In <span style="font-weight: bold;">ALARMS/EVENTS, Search</span><a href="Ricerca__allarmi.htm">, </a>find and print alarms and events that meet search criteria (see chapter Alarm search and <a href="Ricerca__eventi.htm">Event searc</a>h).</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </li>
        </ol>
        <p>For further information, see chapter <a href="Allarmi_e_eventi__concetti_di_base.htm">Alarms and events: basic concepts</a></p>
        <p class="TitoloInterno">
            <img src="../Resources/Images/AAaction.gif" style="border: none;float: none;width: 32px;height: 32px;border-style: none;border-style: none;" width="32" height="32" border="0" /><a name="MonitorareImpianto"></a>Monitoring the site</p>
        <ol style="list-style: decimal;list-style-type: decimal;">
            <li class="p-ActionDetail" value="1">
                <p class="ActionDetail">Check for alarms
                                                            </p>
                <div>
                    <ul style="list-style: disc;" type="disc">
                        <li class="p" value="1">
                            <p>If the icon <img src="../Resources/Images/menusx/multi_icon_y_32x41.png" style="border: none;float: none;border-style: none;border-style: none;width: 32;height: 41;" border="0" /> does not appear on the logon page, check general site or assigned area operations or check alarms.</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </li>
            <li class="p-ActionDetail" value="2">
                <p class="ActionDetail">Display device summary
                                                            </p>
                <div>
                    <ul style="list-style: disc;" type="disc">
                        <li class="p" value="1">
                            <p>In <span style="font-weight: bold;">PLANT</span>, <span style="font-weight: bold;">Devices</span> view the device list with status variables and probes (see chapter <a href="Monitoraggio_dispositivi__introduzione.htm">Site: devices</a>).</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </li>
            <li class="p-ActionDetail" value="3">
                <p class="ActionDetail">View site synoptic maps                                                            </p>
                <div>
                    <ul style="list-style: disc;" type="disc">
                        <li class="p" value="1">
                            <p>In <span style="font-weight: bold;">PLANT</span>, <span style="font-weight: bold;">M<span style="font-weight: bold;">aps</span></span> view the main synoptic map and navigate in other maps to check acquired data (see chapter <a href="Monitoraggio_mappe__introduzione.htm">Maps: synoptic maps</a>).</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                    <table style="border-left-color: #000000;border-left-width: 1px;border-right-color: #000000;border-right-width: 1px;background-color: #c0c0c0;width: 90%;margin-left: 40px;border-spacing: 0px;" cellspacing="0" width="90%" bgcolor="#C0C0C0">
                        <col style="width: 6.855%;" />
                        <col style="width: 93.145%;" />
                        <tr valign="top">
                            <td colspan="1" rowspan="1" style="width: 6.855%;padding-right: 10px;padding-left: 10px;background-color: #cccccc;border-bottom-width: 2px;border-bottom-color: #ffffff;border-bottom-style: Solid;" bgcolor="#CCCCCC" valign="middle" width="6.855%">
                                <p class="Note">
                                    <img src="../Resources/Images/AAinfo.gif" style="border: none;width: 32px;height: 32px;float: none;border-style: none;" width="32" height="32" border="0" />
                                </p>
                            </td>
                            <td colspan="1" rowspan="1" style="width: 93.145%;padding-right: 1px;padding-left: 1px;background-color: #cccccc;border-bottom-style: Solid;border-bottom-color: #ffffff;border-bottom-width: 2px;" bgcolor="#CCCCCC" width="93.145%">
                                <p>Synoptic map structure, aspect and navigation modes depend on the designer. Refer to any instructions for use issued during installation.</p>
                            </td>
                        </tr>
                    </table>
                </div>
            </li>
            <li class="p-ActionDetail" value="4">
                <p class="ActionDetail">Display all devices
                                                            </p>
                <div>
                    <ul style="list-style: disc;" type="disc">
                        <li class="p" value="1">
                            <p>In <span style="font-weight: bold;">PLANT</span>, <span style="font-weight: bold;">Global</span> check the device list with status and main probe values (see chapter <a href="Monitoraggio__pagina_principale.htm">Monitoring: main page</a>). </p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </li>
            <li class="p-ActionDetail" value="5">
                <p class="ActionDetail">Display a device group
                                                            </p>
                <div>
                    <ul style="list-style: disc;" type="disc">
                        <li class="p" value="1">
                            <p>In <span style="font-weight: bold;">PLANT</span>, <span style="font-weight: bold;">Global, &lt;groupName&gt;,</span> check the device list with status and main probe values (see chapter <a href="Monitoraggio__pagina_principale.htm">Monitoring: main page</a>).</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </li>
        </ol>
        <p>For further information, see chapter <a href="Monitoraggio__concetti_di_base.htm">Monitoring: basic concepts</a></p>
        <p class="TitoloInterno">
            <img src="../Resources/Images/AAaction.gif" style="border: none;float: none;width: 32px;height: 32px;border-style: none;border-style: none;" width="32" height="32" border="0" /><a name="RichiedereStampaReport"></a> Printing a HACCP and log report</p>
        <ul style="list-style: disc;" type="disc">
            <li class="p-ActionDetail" value="1">
                <p class="ActionDetail">Printing reports
                                                            </p>
                <div>
                    <ul style="list-style: disc;" type="disc">
                        <li class="p" value="1">
                            <p>In <span style="font-weight: bold;">REPORT</span>, <span style="font-weight: bold;">Report</span> select a report template and indicate the log period.</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </li>
        </ul>
        <p>or</p>
        <ul style="list-style: disc;" type="disc">
            <li class="p-ActionDetail" value="1">
                <p class="ActionDetail">Printing a scheduled report
                                                            </p>
                <div>
                    <ul style="list-style: disc;" type="disc">
                        <li class="p" value="1">
                            <p style="color: #000000;">In <span style="font-weight: bold;">REPORT</span>,  Report <span style="font-weight: bold;">file</span> filter the type of report to be displayed.</p>
                        </li>
                        <ul style="list-style: disc;" type="disc">
                            <li style="color: Transparent;" class="p" value="1">
                                <p style="color: #000000;">For PDF reports, print directly from PlantVisorPRO (see <a href="Config-canali__stampante.htm">Printer setup</a>), 
 </p>
                            </li>
                            <li style="color: Transparent;" class="p" value="2">
                                <p style="color: #000000;">For CSV reports, export or print from remote.</p>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </li>
        </ul>
        <p>For further information, see chapter <a href="Report__concetti_di_base.htm">Report: basic concepts</a></p>
        <p class="TitoloInterno">
            <img src="../Resources/Images/AAaction.gif" style="border: none;float: none;width: 32px;height: 32px;border-style: none;border-style: none;" width="32" height="32" border="0" /><a name="ModificareParametriServizio"></a>Editing service parameters and devices</p>
        <ol style="list-style: decimal;list-style-type: decimal;">
            <li class="p-ActionDetail" value="1">
                <p class="ActionDetail">Checking device status and editing parameters
                                                            </p>
                <div>
                    <ul style="list-style: disc;" type="disc">
                        <li class="p" value="1">
                            <p>In <span style="font-weight: bold;">SITE</span>, <span style="font-weight: bold;">Global</span>, double-click a device, <span style="font-weight: bold;">Main</span> page to:</p>
                        </li>
                        <ul style="list-style: disc;" type="disc">
                            <li class="p" value="1">
                                <p>check device status, </p>
                            </li>
                            <li class="p" value="2">
                                <p>check probe values,</p>
                            </li>
                            <li class="p" value="3">
                                <p>set main parameters,</p>
                            </li>
                            <li class="p" value="4">
                                <p>control the unit (i.e.: reset alarms or turn off the unit)</p>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                        <li class="p" value="2">
                            <p>(see chapter <a href="Monitoraggio-dispositivo__pagina_principale.htm">Monitoring-device: main page</a>)</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </li>
            <li class="p-ActionDetail" value="2">
                <p class="ActionDetail">Editing device parameters (i.e.: setpoint).
                                                            </p>
                <div>
                    <ul style="list-style: disc;" type="disc">
                        <li class="p" value="1">
                            <p>In <span style="font-weight: bold;">PLANT, <span style="font-weight: bold;">Global</span></span> double-click a device, <span style="font-weight: bold;">Parameters page</span>: set service parameters (see chapter <a href="Monitoraggio-dispositivo__parametri.htm">Monitoring- device: parameters</a>)</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="p" value="2">
                            <p>If necessary, propagate the same settings on the same parameters for all similar devices</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </li>
            <li class="p-ActionDetail" value="3">
                <p class="ActionDetail">Editing device group parameters (i.e.: setpoint)
                                                            </p>
                <div>
                    <ul style="list-style: disc;" type="disc">
                        <li class="p" value="1">
                            <p>In <span style="font-weight: bold;">PLANT, Global</span>, <span style="font-weight: bold;">&lt;groupName&gt;</span>,  <span style="font-weight: bold;">Parameters</span> page, set a value on several parameters simultaneously (see chapter <a href="Monitoraggio__parametri.htm">Monitoring: parameters</a>)</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </li>
        </ol>
        <p>For further information, see chapter <a href="Dispositivo__concetti_di_base.htm">Devices: basic concepts</a></p>
